gomodel:SYNGO_3121  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Identified presynaptic profiles in the BMP\"\n- \"Boutons which demonstrated vesicles surrounded by the flocculent DAB precipitate and nearly equal membrane densities on pre- and postsynaptic sides were considered symmetrical (inhibitory) synapses (Fig. 5c, d).\"\n\nNote:\n- GAD1; GAD67 is involved in GABA production. Hence the synapse type was labeled \"GABAergic\".\n- BMP = posterior basomedial nucleus (Amygdala). Experimental description: - \"Ten adult (3-8 months old) male (n = 7) and female (n = 3) heterozygous GAD67-GFP knock-in mice (GAD67-GFP mice) were used for this study.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3121" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
